title: Hamas releases two Americans it held captive in Gaza
description: Judith and Natalie Raanan of Illinois were visiting Israel for a family birthday and the High Holy Days when they were taken captive by the militant group Oct. 7.

title: Russian tycoon claims he is behind Forbes purchase, audiotapes show
description: A Kremlin-connected tycoon claims he is the buyer of Forbes, according to audio and video tapes. The U.S. billionaire organizing the deal says there is no Russian involvement.

title: Russia worked to subvert confidence in election systems, cable says
description: The U.S. intelligence community has routinely highlighted what it says are ongoing Russian efforts to undermine the stability of democratic countries.

title: Argentina’s tear-it-all-down frontrunner connects with angry young men
description: Javier Milei, the Trump- and Bolsonaro-admiring economist who leads polls for the presidential election Sunday, offers inflation-weary Argentines a break from the status quo.

title: Amid Gaza aid delay, protests surge across region
description: Protesters took to the streets from Egypt to Indonesia, in marches held in front of Israeli or U.S. diplomatic missions.

title: Gaza’s aid still blocked at Rafah while ‘heartbroken’ U.N. chief looks on
description: Days after President Biden announced aid for the Palestinians, it remains blocked at the border, held up, according to the Egyptians, by Israeli restrictions.

title: What a ground war in Gaza could look like
description: To dismantle Hamas, the IDF would have to fight in Gaza’s dense neighborhoods, adding to the risks civilians are facing.

title: Biden wants help on migrants, but Mexico faces its own surge
description: In Washington, the immigration debate means the U.S. border and Biden’s policies. But Mexico and the entire migration route are under strain.

title: Historic church sheltering civilians struck in deadly Gaza City blast
description: The Church of St. Porphyrius, Gaza’s oldest active church, was sheltering hundreds of Muslims and Christians displaced by the war, according to religious officials.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Biden sees global threats in Hamas and Russia, as two conflicts rage
description: In an Oval Office speech, the president urged Congress to approve aid for both Israel and Ukraine, saying it would “pay dividends for American security for generations.”

title: After failed referendum, Indigenous Australians ask what’s next
description: After an effort to give Aboriginal Australians a modest voice to parliament was resoundingly rejected, many Indigenous peoples are mulling what they can do next.

title: Putin, flexing U.N. veto, takes aim at global rules
description: Russia’s ability to block substantive action by the U.N. Security Council to stop the war in Ukraine has sparked calls for reform — but change seems impossible.

title: Why the Israel-Gaza war represents a broader crisis for global justice
description: Luis Moreno Ocampo, former prosecutor of the International Criminal Court, says both sides may have committed war crimes, but there’s little appetite for justice.

title: U.S. troops in Middle East face repeated drone attacks amid Gaza war
description: A Navy destroyer in the Red Sea also took down a salvo of cruise missiles and drones launched toward Israel from Yemen, the Pentagon said.
